               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <persName id="t18410823-name-1314" type="witnessName">
                        <interp inst="t18410823-name-1314" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18410823-name-1314" type="surname" value="PERKS"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18410823-name-1314" type="given" value="WILLIAM HENRY"></interp>WILLIAM HENRY PERKS</persName>
                  </hi>. I am in the service of Mr. Benjamin Bullock, who keeps a ham and beef shop, in St. John-street. On the 27th of August, between eleven and twelve o'clock, I was in the back room, and heard a noise, I went into the shop, and saw the prisoner leaning over the counter, and the till was out to its full extent—I asked what he had got in his hand—I found in his right hand three pence, and in his left hand, which he put behind him, a half-crown, a shilling, and a sixpence—I looked into the till, and missed a half-crown from it.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="italic">Prisoner.</hi> The half-crown was my own; my mother sent me with it to buy some ham and beef.</p>
